author: mhagger
msg: Iff a TestCase needs a Sandbox, pass it in as a keyword argument.
Previously TestCase.run() was always passed a tuple argument, which
sometimes (depending on TestCase.need_sandbox()) contained a sandbox.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/svntest/testcase.py (TestCase.need_sandbox,
TestCase.get_sandbox_name): Add docstrings.
(TestCase.run): Make sandbox into a keyword argument, and add a
docstring that tells how the method will be called.
(FunctionTestCase.run): Make sandbox into a keyword argument, and
pass it to the delegate as a keyword argument.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/svntest/main.py (TestRunner.run): Pass
sandbox to test case as a keyword argument.

author: glasser
msg: In svn_repos_replay (and by extension, in svn_ra_replay), send
checksums with apply_textdelta.
(Note 1: to see that this is actually being tested, tweak the
apply_textdelta call to pass some garbage string instead of the right
checksum, and observe that svnsync tests fail.)
(Note 2: we don't pass in the empty file's checksum for
apply_textdelta on new files, because that doesn't seem to be common
in Subversion.)
* subversion/libsvn_repos/replay.c
(path_driver_cb_func): Calculate MD5 checksum of the
delta souce, and pass it to editor->apply_textdelta.
